    "methodology": "Sewage discharge data from Environment Agency EDM annual returns. Total hours and spill events are monitored totals \u2014 coverage expanded from ~860 monitors in 2016 to 14,254 (100%) in 2024. Early years significantly under-count actual discharges. River health from WFD classification (last full assessment 2019). Bathing water classifications under revised Bathing Water Directive (rBWD) from 2015. No 2020 data due to COVID.",
    "knownIssues": [
      "EDM monitor coverage expanded dramatically: 862 in 2016 vs 14,254 in 2024. Year-on-year comparisons must account for this.",
      "River health data last fully updated in 2019 \u2014 no reclassification since.",
      "No bathing water classifications for 2020 (COVID).",
      "Some spill data includes partial-year monitoring (counted pro-rata)."
    ]
